Q4/ Explain about thread synchronization(inter-thread communication) ?
Ans) 

	inter-thread communication :  Inter-thread communication is a mechanism in which a thread is paused running in its critical section 
   ============================== and another thread is allowed to enter (or lock) in the same critical section to be executed.It is 
     							  implemented by following methods of Object class:

			1) wait() .
			2) notify() .
			3) notifyAll() .
	